wiki_catalogs.name: Project Overview
wiki_catalogs.prompt: Create comprehensive content for the Institutional SureShot Scanner project overview. Explain the multi-agent asynchronous scalping system for MetaTrader 5, its purpose as an autonomous trading platform, and relationship to the broader algorithmic trading ecosystem. Document the core architecture including the InstitutionalStrategy orchestrator, PairAgent swarm, and specialized AI agents. Include both conceptual overviews for beginners and technical details for experienced developers. Use terminology consistent with the codebase including terms like 'PairAgent', 'QuantAgent', 'MarketAnalyst', 'ResearcherAgent', and 'CriticAgent'. Provide practical examples demonstrating the system's autonomous operation and real-time capabilities. Document the multi-timeframe approach, institutional risk management features, and real-time monitoring through React dashboard and Telegram alerts.

wiki_overview.content:
<blog>

# Institutional SureShot Scanner - Comprehensive Trading Bot Analysis

## Project Introduction

### Purpose Statement
The Institutional SureShot Scanner is a sophisticated algorithmic trading system designed for high-frequency scalping across multiple financial instruments. Built specifically for Exness MT5 accounts, this system combines machine learning models with advanced risk management to execute automated trading strategies with institutional-grade precision.

### Core Goals and Objectives
- **Multi-Agent Architecture**: Implements a distributed agent system where each currency pair has its dedicated trading agent
- **Machine Learning Integration**: Combines Random Forest, XGBoost, LSTM, and transformer-based models for comprehensive market analysis
- **Advanced Risk Management**: Incorporates institutional-level risk controls including circuit breakers, correlation filters, and volatility-adaptive positioning
- **Real-time Monitoring**: Provides live dashboard visualization through WebSocket connections and REST APIs
- **Self-Learning Capability**: Features automatic model retraining and adaptive parameter optimization

### Target Audience
- Professional traders seeking automated scalping solutions
- Institutions requiring multi-symbol trading automation
- Developers interested in advanced trading bot architectures
- Algorithmic trading enthusiasts working with MT5 ecosystem

## Technical Architecture

### Component Breakdown

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Main Controller] --> B[MT5 Client]
    A --> C[Institutional Strategy]
    A --> D[Auto Trainer]
    
    C --> E[Pair Agents]
    C --> F[Risk Manager]
    C --> G[Market Analyst]
    C --> H[Quant Agent]
    C --> I[Researcher Agent]
    C --> J[Critic Agent]
    
    E --> K[Individual Symbol Analysis]
    F --> L[Position Sizing]
    F --> M[Risk Controls]
    G --> N[Market Regime Detection]
    H --> O[ML Predictions]
    I --> P[Signal Validation]
    J --> Q[Performance Review]
    
    A --> R[Stream Server]
    R --> S[React Dashboard]
    
    T[Model Storage] --> H
    U[News Filter] --> E
    V[Data Cache] --> E
```

### Design Patterns
The system implements several key architectural patterns:

- **Agent-Based Architecture**: Each trading pair operates independently with its own agent
- **Pipeline Pattern**: Sequential processing of data through multiple analysis stages
- **Observer Pattern**: Real-time event broadcasting to dashboard components
- **Factory Pattern**: Dynamic model loading and predictor instantiation
- **Strategy Pattern**: Pluggable risk management and trading strategies

### System Relationships

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Main as Main Controller
    participant Strat as Institutional Strategy
    participant Agents as Pair Agents
    participant Risk as Risk Manager
    participant ML as Quant Agent
    participant MT5 as MT5 Client
    
    Main->>Strat: Initialize Strategy
    Strat->>Agents: Create Pair Agents
    Strat->>Risk: Initialize Risk Controls
    
    loop Every Scan Cycle
        Strat->>Agents: Parallel Scan
        Agents->>ML: Machine Learning Analysis
        ML-->>Agents: Predictions & Scores
        Agents->>Risk: Risk Validation
        Risk-->>Agents: Execution Approval
        Agents->>MT5: Place Orders
        MT5-->>Agents: Order Results
        Agents->>Strat: Status Updates
    end
```

## Key Implementation

### Main Entry Points
- **`main.py`**: Primary application controller orchestrating the entire trading system
- **`main_async.py`**: Alternative async implementation for enhanced performance
- **`dashboard/index.html`**: React-based monitoring interface

### Core Modules
- **`strategy/institutional_strategy.py`**: Central coordinator managing all trading agents
- **`strategy/pair_agent.py`**: Individual symbol-specific trading intelligence
- **`execution/mt5_client.py`**: MT5 terminal connectivity and order execution
- **`utils/risk_manager.py`**: Comprehensive risk control and position management
- **`analysis/quant_agent.py`**: Machine learning model integration and prediction engine

### Configuration Approach
- **`config/settings.py`**: Centralized environment variable management
- **`.env`**: Runtime configuration with MT5 credentials and trading parameters
- **`requirements.txt`**: Python dependency specification

### External Dependencies
```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Python Trading Bot] --> B[MetaTrader5]
    A --> C[pandas/numpy]
    A --> D[scikit-learn]
    A --> E[XGBoost]
    A --> F[PyTorch]
    A --> G[Transformers]
    A --> H[FastAPI/Uvicorn]
    A --> I[React/Vite]
```

### Integration Points
- **MT5 Terminal**: Direct market data access and order execution
- **WebSocket Server**: Real-time dashboard communication
- **Telegram API**: Trade notifications and alerts
- **External News Services**: Economic calendar integration

### Component Relationships

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Main Controller] --> B[Strategy Coordinator]
    B --> C[Parallel Agent Execution]
    C --> D[Individual Symbol Analysis]
    D --> E[ML Model Predictions]
    E --> F[Risk Validation]
    F --> G[Position Sizing]
    G --> H[Order Execution]
    
    I[Dashboard API] --> J[WebSocket Server]
    J --> K[React Frontend]
    
    L[Model Storage] --> M[Quant Agent]
    N[News Filter] --> O[Pre-Scan Validation]
    P[Data Cache] --> Q[Feature Engineering]
```

## Key Features

### Functionality Overview
- **Multi-Timeframe Analysis**: Simultaneous processing of M1, M5, H1, and H4 timeframes
- **Machine Learning Ensemble**: Combined predictions from multiple algorithms
- **Advanced Risk Controls**: Institutional-grade risk management with circuit breakers
- **Real-time Monitoring**: Live dashboard with WebSocket connectivity
- **Self-Learning Models**: Automatic model retraining and parameter optimization

### Implementation Highlights
- **`strategy/features.py`**: Comprehensive technical indicator library
- **`utils/data_cache.py`**: Efficient market data caching system
- **`utils/shared_state.py`**: Cross-process state synchronization
- **`market_data/loader.py`**: Optimized MT5 data retrieval

### Feature Architecture

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Initialization
    Initialization --> SymbolDetection
    SymbolDetection --> AgentCreation
    AgentCreation --> ScanCycle
    
    ScanCycle --> DataCollection
    DataCollection --> MLAnalysis
    MLAnalysis --> RiskValidation
    RiskValidation --> PositionManagement
    PositionManagement --> ScanCycle
    
    ScanCycle --> DashboardUpdate
    DashboardUpdate --> ScanCycle
    
    ScanCycle --> Shutdown
    Shutdown --> [*]
```

The Institutional SureShot Scanner represents a sophisticated trading automation solution that successfully combines modern machine learning techniques with traditional technical analysis and robust risk management. Its modular architecture enables scalability across multiple financial instruments while maintaining real-time responsiveness essential for high-frequency trading environments.

**Sources:**
- [main.py](main.py)
- [config/settings.py](config/settings.py)
- [strategy/institutional_strategy.py](strategy/institutional_strategy.py)
- [strategy/pair_agent.py](strategy/pair_agent.py)
- [requirements.txt](requirements.txt)
- [api/stream_server.py](api/stream_server.py)
- [utils/risk_manager.py](utils/risk_manager.py)
- [execution/mt5_client.py](execution/mt5_client.py)
- [analysis/quant_agent.py](analysis/quant_agent.py)
- [market_data/loader.py](market_data/loader.py)
- [dashboard/package.json](dashboard/package.json)
- [dashboard/src/App.jsx](dashboard/src/App.jsx)
- [dashboard/src/hooks/useBotWebSocket.js](dashboard/src/hooks/useBotWebSocket.js)

</blog>
